    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-07-31T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-07-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="556"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d556">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 822.124/299.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Quito</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-07-31">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 31, 1913</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Congress, which opens August 10, will probably award Guayaquil contract. It
                    might be well for the Department to find out if MacArthur Bros. are in earnest.
                    If so a representative should be sent immediately or the local representative be
                    given full powers to negotiate and sign contract. This firm is the only entirely
                    American house interested.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Schuyler</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
